  "summary": "English Wikipedia currently has 7,141,322 articles and needs 7,160,000 by April 1, 2026 — a gap of 18,678 articles over 37 days, requiring ~505 articles/day. The most recent 114-day measurement (Nov 2025 to Feb 23, 2026) shows only 394 articles/day net growth, which would fall ~4,000 articles short. This is a 3.6-sigma deviation below the 2025 average of 534/day, suggesting a genuine structural decline likely linked to Wikipedia's August 2025 AI content speedy deletion policy. However, month-to-month variance is high (range 428-614/day in 2025), so a single strong month could bridge the gap. The probability hinges on whether the recent decline is persistent or temporarily low — the weight of evidence favors persistence, making YES unlikely but not impossible.",
